Vol / Page:  13
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Beat.</i>-A musterer's <i>b</i>. is the ground off which he has to clear the sheep each day; often top <i>b</i>., bottom <i>b</i>., middle<i> b</i>., etc., also hard and easy <i>bs</i>. The word is also applied to the ground on which a rabbit poisoner has to lay his poison.
