Quote:  <i>Beat</i>. A musterer's<i> beat</i> is the ground off which he has to clear the sheep each day, often <i>top beat, bottom beat, middle beat</i>, etc., also <i>hard</i> and <i>easy beats</i>. The word is also applied to the ground on which a rabbit poisoner has to lay his poison.
